rican hardwood forests, the dynamics of illegal agricultural imports throug=
h the U.S.-Mexican border.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; =
line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">My parents were lifelong civil serva=
nts with the U.S. Department of Agriculture, so the conversations got prett=
y wonky.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;=
 margin: 0 0 1em 0;">For both of my parents, the job was personal.&nbsp;</p=
><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 =
0 1em 0;">My mom was born into a local dairy empire in India, built from a =
rural village in Gujarat and passed down generation after generation until =
my grandfather immigrated with his family to the United States. My dad grew=
 up going to his family&#8217;s dairy, poultry, and produce farms in New En=
gland.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; m=
argin: 0 0 1em 0;">I turned out pretty wonky too.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"colo=
r: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">My path=
 looks eclectic from the outside &#8211; my first startup built open source=
 software infrastructure, then I went back to grad school to work with U.S.=
 military officials on climate risk, and then I worked on water trading in =
the Central Valley.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-he=
ight: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">The common theme connecting all these dots =
is that I&#8217;m driven to solve esoteric societal problems &#8211; prefer=
ably with technology.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-=
height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">There are jobs out there where you can re=
ally make a difference in people&#8217;s lives.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a=
1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;"><strong>III.</s=
trong>&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 2=
6px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Most agriculture today is neither sustainable nor =
